  "texts": [
    "Thus, for any fixed weight matrices {A (m) } m∈ [k], there exists some Y such that it is not output to the residual stream.",
    "C.2 Proof of Theorem 2Theorem 2.",
    "There exists parameter matrices A (1) and A (2) such that, for any permutation matrix P and target matrix Y, a two-layer, decoder-only, attention-only, causal mask-free, transformer parameterized by A (1), A (2) given [P; Y P] as input outputs Y to a block of the residual stream.Proof of Theorem 2.",
    "We proceed by construction.The first layer copies P into the bottom block-row of the residual stream.",
